od,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6b847f8-2ba0-4ab5-a492-b46989baa63c_914x356.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6b847f8-2ba0-4ab5-a492-b46989baa63c_914x356.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6b847f8-2ba0-4ab5-a492-b46989baa63c_914x356.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6b847f8-2ba0-4ab5-a492-b46989baa63c_914x356.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></figure></div><p>等等。</p><p>这不是佩里的错。当他在2018年发布原始图表时，他<a href="https://www.aei.org/carpe-diem/chart-of-the-day-century-price-changes-1997-to-2017/">建议</a>这只是一种<em>可能的</em>解释：</p><blockquote><p>看到任何模式吗？商品（像电视这样的进口竞争）与非交易（如育儿），制造商品（包括服装和汽车的进口竞争）与服务（医疗，医院，教育），竞争性（软件）与受保护的行业（医疗保健） ），政府参与/资金/法规的程度？</p></blockquote><p>但是，“政府参与程度”的解释似乎比“可交易，不可交易”和“制造业与服务”的解释更为流行，尽管后者对许多趋势都是完全合理的解释。</p><p>实际上，当我们仔细观察此图表时，我们会看到“政府参与程度”叙述的许多差异。</p><p>大学教科书没有受到严格的监管，但其价格却大幅上涨 - 至少直到2010年代中期。教科书是通过廉价的学生贷款间接补贴的，但是在政府于2009  -  2012年从私营部门<a href="https://www.mercatus.org/research/data-visualizations/student-loans-held-federal-government">接管</a>学生贷款市场之后不久，其价格实际上<em>停止</em>上涨。</p><p>手机服务受到高度监管，但其价格在图表中下降了。同时，住房可能是现有最受监管的行业，并且还通过税收减免和代金券通过政府补贴，但其价格在给定时间段的工资少于工资少于工资。</p><p>至于大学学费，私立学校的学费比公立学校要高得多，自90年代以来，他们的标价<a href="https://research.collegeboard.org/media/pdf/trends-in-college-pricing-presentation-2023.pdf">上涨了更多的</a>美元。</p><p>实际上，由于法规和补贴的结合，服务很昂贵的流行观念并不能用作伞的解释。正如我去年在一篇文章中所写的那样，在某些情况下，补贴是故事的一部分，在某些情况下，法规是故事的一部分，但是这里有很多细微差别和异质性： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;5a2ca274-a111-4924-9e5e-17c5a878b591&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;In a recent post over at his new substack (which you should check out), Marc Andreessen rails against the exploding prices of big-ticket service industries like college, health care, and child care. He posts the following famous graph from the American Enterprise Institute:&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Why do education, health care, and child care cost so much in America?&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-03-06T09:57:36.719Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7c6c322c-d9a8-4d47-8374-3eb7cf7beb7d_1024x683.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-do-education-health-care-and&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:106662161,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:135,&quot;comment_count&quot;:134,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"></div><p> “政府参与”的故事也没有解释为什么在过去十年中，从90年代末到2010年代初的许多服务都变得<em>越来越</em><em>负担</em>得起： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg" width="656" height="476.6933333333333" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:654,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:656,&quot;bytes&quot;:78904,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd6b2bae-5452-4375-9584-eb130c234223_900x654.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://x.com/jmhorp/status/1750622296283189542">杰里米·霍佩达尔</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>因此，尽管几乎可以肯定的是，政府参与在“世纪图表”的某些价格差异中发挥了作用，但这可能只是许多因素之一。像许多人一样，以图表为简单的“自由主义者是正确的”叙述是一个错误。</p><p>如果这里有一个总体课程，那就是当图表显示许多不同的趋势时，您应该期望这些趋势有几种不同的原因。很少有“一种经济理论来统治所有这些理论”，如果您认为图表已经证明了这种理论的存在，那么您很有可能会误解图表。</p><h4>示例2：生产力与付款</h4><p>在过去的十年中，也许没有像“生产力与付费”图那样在美国话语中具有影响力。该图有很多版本，但我将使用经济政策研究所发布的版本。这可能是图表的最著名版本，这是我们大多数人在2010年代末辩论该问题时使用的版本： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.am