且很难谈论政策，因为一切都取决于谁赢了。尽管如此，在这些艰难时期，我将尽我所能继续为您提供有趣且相关的内容。</p><p>本周的Econ 102剧集以特殊的嘉宾<a href="https://x.com/kylascan">Kyla Scanlon</a>为特色，Kyla Scanlon是Econ作家，他创造了“ VibeSperion”一词，并<em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/This-Economy-Money-Markets-Really/dp/0593727878">在本经济中写了这本书的作者？：货币和市场如何真正起作用</a></em>。我们进行了非常活泼和亲切的讨论！ </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8abc5d6d2fb9a59bcd90652523&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The Vibecession &amp; the Future Economy under Trump vs Biden with Kyla Scanlon&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/5T7C36iReycE9kJZCqxMzc&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/5T7C36iReycE9kJZCqxMzc" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>无论如何，访问本周有趣的事情清单。</p><h4> 1.欧洲开始意识到降解是不好的</h4><p>欧洲议会刚刚举行了选举，每个人都在谈论<a href="https://www.vox.com/politics/354601/european-parliament-elections-macron-afd-national-rally-far-right-fidesz-france">极右翼政党获得了很多基础</a>。但是另一个大故事是绿党的衰落，绿党<a href="https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20240610-green-parties-suffer-eu-poll-drubbing">预计自2019年以来将失去</a>大约四分之一的席位，在法国和德国造成的损失尤其大。 <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/article/2024/jun/09/green-party-losses-in-eu-elections-raise-concerns-over-green-deal">普遍的共识</a>似乎是，欧洲选民不愿意优先考虑与面包和面包问题的斗争：</p><blockquote><p>自2019年上次选举以来，该党的投票份额似乎几乎减半了，在德国，该党的投票份额似乎几乎减半。在法国，最右边的领导者，总统伊曼纽尔·马克龙（Emmanuel Macron） <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/article/2024/jun/09/eu-elections-far-right-gains-germany-austria-netherlands-exit-polls">称SNAP选举</a>，对果岭的支持下降了相同的金额……</p><p> [绿党]传统上受到年轻选民的鼓舞，其中一些选民现在似乎已经转移到了极右翼的替代方案FürDeutschland（AFD）以及更新的政党中……</p><p>政治科学家怀疑，对欧洲气候政策有广泛反对，但警告说，设计良好的措施（尤其是击中最贫穷家庭的措施）可能会适得其反。</p></blockquote><p>尽管似乎没有人使用这个词，但这里的关键问题似乎是<strong>降解</strong>。尽管让人们更加贫穷的人打击气候变化的想法似乎并没有扎根在美国（除了偶尔在《纽约时报》上<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/08/books/review/shrink-the-economy-save-the-world.html">发光的非批判性文章</a>之外），欧洲知识分子似乎发现这个概念<a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/energy/fossil-fuel-centred-growth-is-obsolete-says-eus-von-der-leyen-2023-05-15/">很诱人</a>。一些绿党支持者甚至断言他们的政党失去了，因为他们没有足够努力地推动降解： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F612b36b2-cccd-4728-a8a6-e9f13a46713b_755x800.jpeg" width="586" height="620.9271523178808" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws